I've tried doing it by manually erasing some rows on the database, but what happens is that these changes do not get published to other peers on other sites. (Which means that they can still see the topics.)
&nbsp;
I had a look at content.json and noticed that there's an Ignore: function that tells ZeroNet not to sign and not to publish anything inside the data/users/ folder, so once you click on Sign .. the console says [SKIPPED] data/users/zerotalk.db for example.
&nbsp;
It is tempting to remove this Ignore function, but I'm afraid it will screw up the whole site. Might have to test this on a dummy site, but some input on the matter would be much appreciated. We really need a universal Admin interface.. otherwise we will succumb to spammers and trollers:

https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/issues/354

