Got it to work now. The file you have to modify is inside **/data/users/content.json.** That's where you'll find user_contents. Wish this was made more specific on the docs.

In this case, I added Kopykate@zeroid.bit to the permissions.. and set the max_size to 100kb (100,000 bytes, as shown below). 

The size limit applies to basically everything that is inside your user-specific folder, except for the content.json. The data.json file will include topics and comments, as commonly employed on blogging/talk site clones. Everything else such as gifs and videos will also take up space.

 "user_contents": {
  "cert_signers": {
   "zeroid.bit": [ "1iD5ZQJMNXu43w1qLB8sfdHVKppVMduGz" ]
  },
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 40000
   },
   "bitid/.*@zeroid.bit": { "max_size": 40000 },
   "bitmsg/.*@zeroid.bit": { "max_size": 15000 }
  },
  "permissions": {
   "bad@zeroid.bit": false,
   "kopykate@zeroid.bit": { "max_size": 100000 }
  }
 }
}
